    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-14T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1998a Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T01:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 14, 1937—1 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>214. In order that no possible measures of precaution may be omitted, it is
                    suggested that you take steps towards seeing that American nationals at and
                    around Shanghai be informed, through whatever agency you deem practicable, of
                    sailing dates and accommodations available on merchant vessels, of which any who
                    may desire to leave, especially women and children, might take advantage.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
